Many hospitals are economy on disinfectants
This year, more than a thousand infections, caused mainly by the incorrect use of antibiotics, have been recorded in hospitals.
The hygiene conditions of hospitals, the insufficient number of beds, the overwork medical staff do not help has block infections, says the chief doctor of the national centre for epidemiology.
Many hospitals are also the economy on disinfectants
There is no long an infection MRSA has been diagnosed in the service of Traumatologie hospital János.
The bacteria resistant to antibiotics was detected on a man in hospital following a serious accident.
The patient has been isolated.
At the beginning of the year a similar infection in 2006 place.
The injured from a serious car accident left the hospital but little time he Apres of return because of an infection MRSA and, since then, doctors have not been able to make a significant operation because of the bacteria in his body.
Until 10 December of this year, 1 094 infections Hospitalieres generated by an agent Pathogene Multirésistant have been declared the Systeme national monitoring nosocomial, has indicated Karolina Böröcz doctor, chief of the national centre for epidemiology.
Has aware that this is the number of infections caused by an agent Pathogene Multirésistant which has really been made in hospitals and for the rest we have no information.
Around two-thirds of the infections (683 infections) have been caused by the MRSA, in other words by the staphylococcus aureus resistant has the Méthicilline-oxacilline.
A third of people are carriers of the bacterium staphylococcus aureus (its) in their nose without develop a disease.
Infections caused by its (such as Angines, Amygdalites, infections, skin infections traumatic) respond well to antibiotics, they are easily cured.
However, if the antibiotics are used to Maniere excessive or inappropriate, the bacteria, which reacts well to antibiotics, develop a good bacteria resistant to antibiotics which Proliférera quickly in poor conditions Hospitalieres.
In the event of poor functioning provisional or extended the immune Ltd, this bacteria can cause infections Hospitalieres serious, such as an infection or a traumatic endotoxic, on the sick older, small weight or with a body weakened.
According to the doctor director of the hospital János, there is nothing particularly in infection MRSA, these infections are parts of the daily hospitals.
We must not confuse the infection with the epidemic, there is no MRSA only or they are not seeking, said Tibor Nyulasi.
The its resistant to antibiotics.
"These patients are isolated, carers sets of rubber gloves and masks protection and we have antibiotics suited to the cure", said Tibor Nyulasi.
In principle, the patients in hospitals are examined if they are carrying MRSA, but the infection can not always be avoided.
The Prélevement of the sample is not the way
The vast majority of infections caused by MRSA could be prevented but the conditions and the circumstances are not favourable in hospitals, Hungarian, to prevent the development and proliferation of agents Pathogenes resistance, says Karolina Böröcz.
As this infection is manifested above all in hospitals and in homes for the elderly, hospitals should monitor the sick hospital and isolate the sick immediately carry MRSA.
However, the Prélevement microbiological is not the way in hospitals Hungarian.
We must bear in mind that the cash national social security fund these examinations.
Most cases does not see the day that if the infection MRSA is detectable on the patient, said the doctor chief of epidemiological centre.
The European Union has stringent recommendations on the appropriate use of antibiotics in human medicine and there are directives Hungarian also for curing infections and syndromes.
We must make efforts to that antibiotic therapy is targeted, in other words microbiological examinations should be made to Empecher resistance to medicines hospitals but not always take account.
Achieving Prélevements microbiological is even more rare in outpatient care and care basis, reported Karolina Böröcz.
Many hospitals are economy on disinfectants
Scientific evidence shows that MRSA Proliferent a patient has another more often through the medical staff.
It is therefore important to wash their hands, to put gloves and masks protection, but considerable gaps are detected in hospitals in this area.
The MRSA Proliferent by infection transmitted by inhalation of droplets and by contact, but because of the conditions in the hospitals Hungarians, the patient contaminated can not always be isolated.
Moreover, the rooms are often full, the beds are often too ESRP each other when in terms of the epidemic, patients should be far apart from each other to 1.5 metres to a minimum.
Unfortunately, we also note as hospitals, situation Financiere difficult, cut back on disinfectants, they lack Infirmieres, the sick are many, and the risk of infection is even greater, said Karolina Böröcz.
According to Karolina Böröcz, in hospitals or the preventive measures are complied with, the number of infections is lower of Maniere demonstrable or the proliferation of the agent Pathogene can be blocked.
Draft government against MRSA
The treatment of the infection MRSA is spending exorbitant funds for social security, that is why we fight everywhere against this infection.
In England, for example, the government has established a programme to prevent or reduce the incidence of MRSA.
According to information published, this programme is effective and infection MRSA show a declining trend in England.
The European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control (ECDC) revealed among its priorities the prevention of the impact of agents Pathogenes resistance (such as MRSA) and also the prevention of infections Hospitalieres caused by these agents Pathogenes.
