As he said, their risk analysis is published every year and if events taking place that could have an impact on the change of the risk, they inform public opinion, as in this case, by issuing a warning of risk.
The Fete is not marked in red everywhere
In Hungary, the law defines exactly the days of Fete and, around Fetes, it has become aware of reorganising the working days which will reduce the number next year.
The Fetes are not uniform in the EU and the us either.
The Hungarian legislation distinguishes the days of Fete national and state and day of rest.
The days of rest are often linked has Fetes religious or has important historic events.
In Hungary, we Fetons the new year, the last day of the year ends and the first day of the new year are also days rest, all the more so that the Réveillonneurs can rest in peace.
Moreover, in a year, we have in any eleven Fetes marked in red.
On 15 March is a Fete national commemoration of the revolution of 1848, as the 23 October which is also the commemorative day of the revolution of 1956.
The 20 Aout, we Fetons the constitution of our State, 1 May is the Fete labour and on 1 and 2 November, we remember the members of our family and friends who have died.
In addition, we have two days has Easter, the whit and Christmas.
The days of our Fetes State, national or religious rarely falls on a weekend, according to the timetable, it has become aware of reorganising the working days in the case or it is a working day before or Apres the Fete marked in red.
It is true that we are paying the price of weekend sustained by working or going has school on Saturday before the weekend extended.
For many years, the Labour Minister statue in Regulation Particuliere on the days of replacing days before or after the Fetes.
The law extends to all employers and employees for all their employees, on the officials and the people working in the public service.
It does not apply, however, to the service companies, institutions turning point and without a break in service, by their vocation, and also for the days of rest.
This year, the working days will be modified only around Fetes of the end of the year, from 24 December, life is private almost throughout the country because according to the most people experience rather overtime or taking holidays they have saved has these purposes in order to move the days between Christmas and the day of the new year at home.
Next year many Fetes fall in the middle or at the end of the week, so there will be fewer changes in working days compared to this year.
The timetable will be reorganised the premiere time around the Fete labour to enable employees to stay at home four days of Affilé.
On Saturday 25 April will be a working day for a day of rest on Friday 2 May.
Another change is scheduled for October 23: on Saturday 18 October will be a working day replacing the Friday 24.
On the other hand, next year, the end of the year ahead in the context of Fetes as from 24 December, everyone will pause non-stop 2006 if the day of the new year falls on a Wednesday.
