Yesterday, the Czech government ministers have signed nine in any operational programmes with representatives of the European Commission, which could, in the coming years, provide 14 billion (around EUR 365 billion kronor Czech) to the Czech Republic.
This is almost half of the total sum that the Czech Republic can obtain Brussels in the years 2007 to 2013.
