The Court of Appeal of Nicaragua confirmed on Thursday sentenced to 20 years in prison for the former President of the country Arnold Alemán, to which he was sentenced in 2003 for fraud of $100 million (nearly 1.8 billion kronor).
However, later it was released and lived under house arrest in his Hacienda near the capital city of Nicaragua.
