According to Klaus, it is not only the structure of the conference, made up of a curious mixture of representatives of governments and non-governmental organizations, which is unacceptable, but also the basic difference between the rhetoric and the accompanying reality.
"The debate is not structured at all, it is only a rocket words, ersatz solutions to the current problems," said Klaus.
The Czech President has pointed out, when presenting his book, that it has great importance for him and that is why it is committed to this cause.
It has also expressed its satisfaction that his book also appears in German translation, because, he said, "I often meeting that the caricature of my views".
Now, those interested can read its positions without being distorted.
Klaus pointed out that although it is not weatherman, it has nevertheless, in his opinion, enough provisions to draw up such a white.
This is an academic able to follow and assess Treaties scientists, it has the practice of the statistical and it is also an economist.
The major conclusions of the books, is, according to him, the arguments: climate change is constantly evolving, it is normal there is no view of all researchers on climate change, the effects of the current changes are neither too high nor too serious, they do not represent any danger and, finally, the efforts made to influence climate change are unnecessary, inefficient and unacceptably expensive.
