This calculation takes into account the unwanted pregnancies (24%) and the birth poorly planned or occurred so unexpected.
Even today, more than a pregnancy on three (36%) is not provided, reveals a study carried out by the National Institute of demographic studies (Ined), forty years after the vote on the law Neuwirth which has liberalized contraception in France.
This calculation takes into account the unwanted pregnancies (24%) and the birth poorly planned or occurred so unexpected.
The various methods of contraception such as the pill or the Stérilet are still a failure rate of 5% to 6%, believe the Ined.
The liberalisation of contraception helped better "control of fertility", according to the Institute which note that the rate of use of the pill among women 20 to 44 years rose from 5% in 1970 to 60% today.
Finally, eight out of ten births would be planned today.
Even calculated the months closely for a couple on five and if possible in the spring, season judged as the more pleasant for having a child.
Spectacular repairs on the space station
It took more than seven hours of work in the area to the astronaut Scott Parazynski and his fellow crew of the international space station (Iss) to carry out the spectacular repair a solar panel torn apart, essential to the pursuit of scientific activities of the station.
A way out risky who has accumulated records because of its duration, its remoteness habitable modules, the speed with which it was conceived, tools' designer' by the astronauts to carry out repairs.
The problem became apparent Tuesday when the astronauts had unloaded the shuttle discovery the module harmony, a big piece Cylindrique to welcome soon scientific laboratories European and Japanese (see controlled).
This module is a kind of shore of Appontage for Modules-laboratoires.
But we have to be able to supply them with electricity.
The second task of the crew was to move a module of electricity generation by solar panels weighing 17.5 tonnes, already present on the Iss, to put it to post on its final position.
Having moved, the crew began the redeployment of solar panels module which have a scale of 76 metres.
And this is where one of the panels, which Déplient as Accordéons, has been damaged on nearly a metre by a cable that has stuck.
The deployment has been stopped so as not to damage more the trap.
The astronauts, which were originally carry out a way out of control of the shuttle discovery, then go repair another sign solar whose rotating system was defective, have been forced to devote themselves to the panel damaged.
And this is Scott Parazynski which has been chosen to go Caracoler at the end of 30 metres in length of arm Télécommandé of the shuttle added to the station to carry out repairs.
This is one of the best' Spacewalker' (space traveller) by NASA.
Great, resistant, appropriate, it has the bare-chested highly developed and long arms.
For 46 years, this doctor training has been given the task of' make' the trap solar' injured'.
After precisely inspected the damage, it has compartmentalized cable wrong and has installed kinds of "Attelles" in the area damaged.
It was helped by a second "Spacewalker' remained close to the SAS and, from within, by other astronauts whose Peggy Whitson, the commander of the crew.
The tool that he used, a Minicanne of hockey shrouded in order to avoid isolating the electrocution on the solar panels producing several hundred volts, has been designed and "cobbled together by the astronauts on board the station.
Once the operation is over, Scott Parazynski waited that the trap is fully deployed before making an inventory of its tools and regain within the station.
Yesterday afternoon, the astronauts benefited of half a day of relaxation before today, seven astronauts will make up the shuttle discovery for a return to earth planned on Wednesday.
The title EADS punished in stock market
The action EADS is in net decline on the Paris stock exchange, after the group of aerospace and defence has announced that he would have to spend between 1.2 and 1.4 billion euros to deal with the late m.
EADS loses 4% to 21.96 euros on the Paris stock exchange.
The group was forced to review its forecast of operational result for 2007 as a result of the delays caused by the slow progress of the development of the engine of the m, which determines the inaugural flight of the aircraft.
The cost to compensate for the delay in the delivery of its military transport aircraft, announced in October, is "between 1.2 and 1.4 billion more than EUR 1 billion for Airbus' home, announced mother European manufacturer EADS.
Because of these charges, EADS will be forced to announce new targets result of exploitation (Ebit) for 2007 when it presents its quarterly results next Thursday, adds without more specific figures.
The group also stated that the estimate of new charges is consistent with the delay of six months.
For the record, the result of operational EADS fell by 86% in 2006, mainly because of charges for delays of another programme, the very large - bearer.
Originally, the group included a first delivery of the m to the French army in October 2009.
The choice of the status quo
There will be no suspense Sunday, exit polls: the Russians will opt overwhelmingly for the party of President Putin, United Russia.
Confirming their desire for stability, or even to authoritarianism, after a campaign very locked.
Three days of parliamentary elections, Russian President Vladimir Putin addressed today a message to voters television on public service broadcasting, already registered but whose contents are kept secret.
It is as high on the list of United Russia, the Pro-Kremlin party whose victory looks overwhelming.
Yesterday, the President has not revealed by receiving the ambassadors foreigners, simply to give a new charge against the West accused of interference - his favourite subject during the campaign.
"We know the price of a true democracy and want fair elections, the more transparent and open elections smoothly", he added.
In the eyes of the opposition, there is still a long way to go.
It denounces a campaign tainted pressure.
The Communist leader Gennady Zuganov said that there has been no' elections also dirty, even at the time of Yeltsin.
After the repression of demonstrations last weekend, the former World Chess Garry Kasparov, sentenced to five days in prison for illegal demonstration, remains forbidden to visit according to his lawyer.
"The Russians have kept the mentality of homo Sovieticus'
Behind these legislative without suspense are appearing two issues much more open:
- successor to Putin to the Presidency?
The Official Journal published yesterday the date of the first round of the presidential, on 2 March 2008; the candidates have until 23 December to make known.
Voted in 2000 and re-elected in 2004, Vladimir Putin can not run for a third term in a row.
But no successor has emerged.
- what role will play Putin after March?
Prime Minister?
leader of the parliamentary majority and the all-powerful Party United Russia which choose the government and the President?
In any case, the legislative and the presidential power outgoing win.
It is a tradition.
"The Russians have kept the mentality of homo Sovieticus, they do not feel masters of their own destiny, believe the sociologist Lev Goudkov, Director of the Centre independent Levada.
The historian Nikolaï Kopossov, of the University of State St Petersburg, goes back further: civil society has been delayed in that country Christianisé five centuries after Europe; the famous Community spirit has delayed the formation of individualism.
After the liberal reforms of the 1990s, Putin has brought the model of a paternalistic State, fully accepted by the population all the more that this new paternalism has not been followed by terror, but by a certain ease economic' estimates Maria Lipman, of the Carnegie Foundation.
Today the Russians' to renounce voluntarily personal responsibility "that they had briefly shown after the collapse of the USSR.
"What is the point of thinking?'
The phenomenon affects all social classes, including the world affairs.
And the elite administrative intends to preserve the status quo: 65 governors (on 85 heads of Russian regions) are leading the local lists of United Russia.
The new freedoms imported from the West are often synonymous with chaos, as in the 1990s.
Opinion prefer stability.
On behalf of what the Russians will not vote for the extremists.
Conclusion of Tamara Tcherednitchenko, a professor of 54 years: "What is the point of thinking?
Those who are in power are not too bad, why change them? "
A heavy memory
After more than 60 years of confidentiality, the Nazi archives of bad Arolsen, which below the fates of 17.5 million victims of the Hitler regime, are free access.
The 47 million documents archives, stored on 27 km of linear to bad Arolsen (Hesse) so far, were able to see that in a' humanitarian', in other words, individually and naming, on request of a former victim or of its eligible parties.
The eleven States responsible for their management about Germany, France, Israel and the Etats-unis- agreed in May 2006 for the open to researchers and historians.
The process of ratification of this agreement by all the States being completed, openness is effective since yesterday.
Sensitive information
The access of historians to bad Arolsen will carry out research "in particular on the movement of prisoners, the population of the camps and the state of health of workers forced', explains Reto Meistern, the director of these archives managed by the International Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC).
Until recently, several countries, including Germany, were opposed to the opening to the public of these documents roll-call, because of the sensitivity of certain information.
As the supposed homosexuality or mental disability of some victims of the deportation.
The registers of concentration camps or arrest warrants issued by the Gestapo had been gathered after war in a practical goal: restoring civilians deported or subject to forced labour and possibly provide evidence of their internment, in order to pave the way for their compensation.
Yet today to bad Arolsen, more than 300 employees permanent deal with tens of thousands of individual requests.
However, for some of the scientific community, access to bad Arolsen interest is limited.
"There is nothing fundamentally new to wait for these documents," said in 2006 Professor Wolfgang Benz, Director of the Centre for research on Anti-Semitism at the Technische Universität Berlin.
The EU and India want to reach a free trade agreement in 2008
Currently, the bilateral trade Indo-européen already reached almost EUR 60 billion per year.
The EU is the largest trading partner of India and represents 18% of its external trade.
The European Union and India hope to sign a free trade agreement in 2008, have indicated the European Commissioner for Trade Peter Mandelson and his Indian counterpart, Kamal Nath.
The EU Foreign Ministers had given the green light in April to the European Commission to negotiate with a view to signing free trade agreements (FTA) with India, South Korea and the Association of South-East Asian Nations (ASEAN) the bilateral trade Indo-européen already reached almost EUR 60 billion per year.
The EU is the largest trading partner of India and represents 18% of its external trade.
Read is also his first foreign investor, but India is only the ninth trading partner of the EU, according to figures of the European Commission.
"A free trade pact will boost greatly the two economies' and' India would improve its access to a market of 450 million Europeans prosperous", has justified Peter Mandelson.
Europe is the first or the second market for each of the first ten products exported by India, the Commissioner Européen.les giants Asian and European traded annually on' 47 billion euros of goods EUR 10 billion' and for' services,' said this week Université Smadja, the head of the European Commission delegation in New Delhi, regretting that bilateral trade has not reached its potential ". EU and India find themselves on Friday for their eighth Summit in New Delhi diplomatic Prime Minister Manmohan Singh and the President of the European Commission José Manuel Durao Barroso.
