A new festival is being set up
As a result of many rumours about the creation, by C 3 presents, a new music festival in Philadelphia, the promoter / producer announcement the Vineland music festival in New Jersey, in partnership with festival producer Republic British Melvin Benn.
"For our company, it is an honour to work with someone who has, no more and no less, inspired the movement current festivals in America," has given Charlie Jones of C 3 to Billboard.com.
C 3 product the festival Lollapalooza Chicago and the Austin city limits music festival.
Vineland, New Jersey, is a destination for the summer campsite.
The festival should be held from 8 to 10 August on a private firm to 500 acres in about 40 minutes Philadelphia.
Once known as the mean fiddler, the director of festival Republic, Melvin Benn, is one of the producers of festivals the most respected in the world.
In 1989, he took the helm of the reading festival in the United Kingdom, which draws annually some 80 000 people.
In 1999, Melvin Benn added the Leeds festival to its portfolio and then, in 2006, festival Republic has created the latitude festival of Henham park in Suffolk.
Since 2002, as Copropriétaire, Melvin Benn was also responsible for the production, the granting of licences and organisational tasks of Glastonbury festival, which can now take up to 177 500 people.
As Glastonbury of "event most inspiring' which it has ever seen, Charlie Jones of C 3 said that his business and Melvin Benn work in parallel to give the region a Festival-événement of European style.
"We had chosen Philadelphia as market and work diligently with the Fairmount parks Commission to create a festival in downtown Philadelphia, supports Charlie Jones.
"We were in talks with the city and the Commission was motivated and enthusiastic about this project.
Unfortunately, we are stuck in Politicailleries because the current administration, is continuing Charlie Jones.
"Fortunately, we were able to discuss with Melvin Benn and we are about to create a superb festival on a site exceptional, Ultimement, will serve as the population of Philadelphia."
C 3 presents has revived the festival Lollapalooza in 2005 to grant park Chicago, after outspoken in the landscape of festivals in 2002 with the Austin city limits music festival.
The two events have made gross income of $9,8m and 11,3m $in 2007.
These two festivals are held in urban areas.
"The European model of Melvin Benn is a festival Champêtre, while ours have rather take place in urban green spaces," said Charlie Jones.
The aim is to merge, one way or another, the two formulas both to give an impression of festival Champêtre to the European and urban America. "
Vineland is about halfway between Philadelphia and Atlantic City.
"The Community of Vineland, including the mayor, enthusiastically supports the holding of this event," said Charlie Jones.
It refuses to reveal the terms of the agreement, but says "that they are sufficiently interesting to allow to invest in such an event and to host a festival which, hopefully, will have a long life."
Charlie Jones said that the reception capacity of this festival is "very great, like that of 80 000 people of Bonnaroo music festival in Tennessee.
It said that invitations have been launched groups, but that nothing could be confirmed at the time to go under press.
"Vineland will be to flavour rock, but the music will be diverse, in the hope to attract all kinds of viewers," said Charlie Jones.
Its partners to C 3, which has received the prize top independent promoter of the last billboard touring awards, are Charlie Walker and Charles Attal.
