Will there be a rally of the end of the year on the stock exchange? experts divided by the crisis of Sub-primes.
In less than five weeks of the close of the financial year, investors are already rubbing their hands in the hope the arrival of the traditional rally of the end of the year.
However, this year the experts are not certain that this will happen.
Banif believes that "from the point of view statistical December, the stock market has generally good behavior.
However, we should not make forecasts exclusively based on statistics, since that given the current context, the uncertainties lurk on the markets, at least in the short term ".
Although they are not supporters to take stock of the momentum in the remaining weeks of the year, these experts point out that "the stock market is fueled by the existence of liquidity, prepared to invest in view of the lack of alternatives with guarantees, especially the fixed income, affected by the effect of flight towards values of quality both in the long periods that in the short".
For this, they believe that the stock market will behaviour rather side-impact, not free of unpredictability "above all because it does not know the impact of the fall in rates likely the Fed, given the high level of gross and the danger of the promotion of inflationary pressures'
Javier Barrio, responsible for sales of Bpi in Spain, agrees that this is not the time to say that there will be a rally.
"It is not the best thing', provides the expert.
The ibex share index Spanish, has lost nearly 4% since 8 November when the index closed to 15.945,7 points.
However, all the experts have this vision negative.
Juan Solana, analyst of Intermoney, believes that the ibex 35 could close the year to 16,000 points with the reorganization of the portfolios and the contributions traditional pension schemes which occur every year during these dates.
However, the expert nuance that things will be a little different this year because he believes that the rally will take place from the second week of December, after the bridge of the celebration of the Constitution (6 December).
The analyst does not consider that the volatility affect the trend of the market.
For its part, Federico Olucha, analyst of Banco Inversis, assesses that we are close to technical levels and "that is why we could see a turn of events of the index which could be caused According to information coming to the European Union with regard to the impact of the crisis on the credit market".
The analyst hope that they will be positive.
Analysts agree to choose the values that will be responsible for the ibex towards new Cottes maximum.
Solana, Intermoney, "says that this year the great values are back to him".
The expert included in the portfolio the two major banks and a few manufacturers' because when the date approaches, the electricity sector will be very expensive. "
While, Federico Olucha, Inversis Banco ensures that the increases will be of the Bank and the industrial sector.
The shipbuilding will also be able to benefit from this rally, if they go ahead.
"ACP for several months recovering positions and we hope that the other shipbuilding as Ferrovial and FCC Suiveront the same way," explains the expert.
The cyclical consumption will lead in the last part of the year due to the increase in sales in the season of Christmas sales.
On the other hand, the expert believes that technological companies will do as well, although in this case there is little representation on the Spanish market.
Five times for seven years
During the past seven years, only two occasions during the month of December has been a month Baissier.
The rally genuine new year took place in 2003, exercise during which the stock markets have come out of the crisis triggered by the construction of the technological bubble.
This year, during which the ibex 35 has recovered 28,17%, the month of Dicembre has seen an increase in 6,68%.
It remains to be seen whether 2007 is the fifth consecutive year of gains (at the moment the ibex rose by 8,36% since January) and if it is successful to computer on its rally of the end of the year.
The People's Bank open 200 offices open 12 hours from Monday to Saturday
The People's Bank has decided to renovate a large part of its offices.
A total of 200 banks are located in the areas most trade of Spain.
These branches, which operate under the popular brand Max, for the Bank represent a great change.
As for the rest of the bodies Spanish, because it is the first group which has decided to begin betting on the opening of uninterrupted its agencies until 8.30 p.m., and to open up the Saturday of 10 to 8.30 p.m..
Another group which has also reiterated several times that he would like to increase the hours of its branches, gone, although it has not yet decided to take the first step.
It is about to conclude an agreement with the trade unions to close 75% of its agencies on Saturday instead to launch an afternoon, but not to the public.
The results of the experience of the People's Bank will be decisive for that other bodies or not adhere to this initiative, which coincides with the working hours of shops.
It is precisely this objective that the People's Bank research.
Attract customers autonomous circulating in these areas to make their purchases in SMEs and businesses street chosen to open up.
The bank wants to open up these 200 agencies established on all of Spain in about 18 months, since this is not the opening of new agencies but a renewal of the existing ones.
For this, the body will update branches that it has already in the trade areas, adapting profile of customers of different streets.
In this way, the increase working hours is accompanied by a different view of the interior of the branch and to a new design, more topical, with colours more light.
The head of commercial bank, ángel Rivera, ensures that this renewal does not involve any major investment, but the recruitment of staff, as the number of employees will increase from six to eight or nine by Agency.
The agencies, which will also spaces for SMEs can meet here, will sell products not financial.
A positive experience for the Group
The People's Bank has already tested its initiative in three agencies in Madrid.
And the experience has been positive, as explained ángel Rivero.
The branches street Murillo brave, O'Donnell and Gran Vía Madrid are the streets to have been chosen, and successfully Apparement, according to Rivero.
The People's Bank has currently 2 500 branches.
