In any case Solbes said in the corridors of Congress that "Although the figure is not good" the differential inflation of Spain on Monetary Union continues to be "more or less" the same as in recent years.
It has also explained that in November "there has been less surprised" that during the previous months, when the government was not faced with such a high increase.
"We expected a figure of around 4%", has recognised the Minister of the economy in relation to the data announced today.
