The climate of Venus could prove to be the future of the earth.
Scientists have said yesterday that Venus has certainly been a world pleasant to live.
The data from the European vessel in orbit have shown that the world is certainly two times smaller than the earth, contrary to what was thought before.
Venus is the planet closer to the earth.
These two worlds are almost the same size, with similar orbits, although Venus is closer to the sun.
Scientists now believe that billions of years, Venus could have had conditions similar to those of the earth, and may even have been habitable.
But the effect global warming because carbon dioxide, the erosion air Dûe the solar radiation allied to a rotation slower Venus has led to a different kind of development.
Today the world is deprived of water, is ravaged by hurricanes and storms of flash and has a surface temperature hot enough to melt lead.
The discoveries from express the probe of the European Space Agency, who has studied the planet for a year, offers a sad vision of the future potential of the land due to the changes catastrophic climate.
Professor of the department of physical Oxford University, Fred Taylor, one of the leaders of the mission from the express, said: "We are beginning to understand why the climate of Venus is so different from that of the earth, although the planets in even they are almost similar.
"Our new data allow us to establish a scenario that there are billions of years, Venus originally would have been similar to the earth, can be even with a surface habitable."
