Venus is the twin infernal of the earth.
Despite its atmosphere hostile to life, Venus resembles more land than we thought until now, the European space probe "from" express has discovered flash in the atmosphere and Tourbillons of wind the Poles, similar to those that appear on the ground in the winter.
For almost three decades, scientists assume that there are flash on Venus.
The European probe "from express" has demonstrated today - it has detected electromagnetic waves to the limits of the atmosphere: the flash on Venus break out to a height of about 56 kilometres of cloud in cloud, relates Christopher Russell of the University of California at Los Angeles in the scientific magazine "nature".
According to the famous theory of the Cyprine, the Flash would have revealed the life on earth: the storm would have stimulated reactions in the oceans that led to the formation of amino acids, the cornerstone of life.
This is not the case on Venus: "If there was life, it must have been a date to ancient history", explains Sean Solomon of the "Carnegie institution in Washington.
Today there should be little things living on the surface of Venus: the atmosphere is about a hundred times more dense that on earth, there is sometimes temperatures of 500 degrees.
"Venus is perhaps the twin infernal of the land, but it remains a twin," said Russell.
Why Venus, so that looks like to land mass and dimensions, was hit development also different, is the fundamental question of the ESA mission.
The departure of "from express" in November 2005 was an important step in the research Vénusienne, since no probe was under way for the Exploration of the world since the 1980s ten.
According to the researchers, the most recent research results which have now been presented in several articles of "nature" point out not only the uniqueness of Venus in the solar system.
They also show that the similarities with the land of our Planéte neighbouring are supposed to greater numbers than at first sight.
And researchers have found, in addition to the Tourbillons of wind already known to the North Pole, an eddy of clouds at the south Pole, which turns much more quickly.
The phenomenon reminds currents of air in the hemispheres land in winter, writing a team of researchers around Giuseppe Piccioni of the Di Astrofisica Spaziale E Fisica Cosmica Italian.
The second Planéte of Sytème solar has almost the same mass that the earth and is, with a diameter of 12.100 kilometres, almost as great.
The Planéte called Star of the evening or the morning revolves around the sun in just 225 days.
However, it does move much more slowly on itself: a day Vénusien hard 243 days landowners.
Although Venus, with temperatures on the surface of 460 degrees Celsius and pressure of 92 bar, hardly ever calls the earth, scientists assume that the two Planétes have set in similar conditions.
On the two, water has accumulated and remained on the ground in the form of oceans, but has lost in space on Venus.
And while carbon dioxide has set itself on the ground in the form of, it is on Venus most of the atmosphere.
